# Feature: Eco Rating

## Score Formula
```
eco_score (0–10) = Σ(sub_score_i × weight_i)
```

| Sub-Score | Weight | Good Threshold | Source (mock → production) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Energy (kWh/room-night) | 25% | < 40 = 10pts | Seed JSON → MESH |
| Water (L/room-night) | 20% | < 150 = 10pts | Seed JSON → MESH |
| Waste Diversion % | 20% | > 75% = 10pts | Seed JSON → MESH |
| Certifications | 15% | LEED/Green Key = 10pts | Seed JSON → MESH Scorecard |
| Carbon Offset Program | 10% | true = 10pts | Seed JSON → CAP Database |
| F&B Sourcing Score | 10% | > 8 = 10pts | Seed JSON → SPROUT |

Each sub-score is normalized to 0–10 before weighting.

## Green Points Multiplier
- Score ≥ 8.0 → +900 bonus points (base 3000 + 900)
- Score 6.0–7.9 → +300 bonus points (base 3000 + 300)
- Score < 6.0 → no bonus

## Eco Badges
- "Green Stay" → stay completed at a hotel with score ≥ 8
- "Eco Warrior" → 3× Green Stay badges earned
- Brand badges: stay at Element/Westin/Ritz with score ≥ 8 → brand-specific badge

## Components to Build
- `EcoScoreRing` — circular SVG ring, colored by score (green/yellow/red), score in center
- `EcoSubScoreBreakdown` — accordion with 6 sub-scores, bar indicators, production source label
- `EcoPointsCallout` — "Book this hotel, earn +900 Bonvoy Green Points" banner
- `EcoBadgeDisplay` — badge shelf on profile page
- `DataSourceNote` — small footnote: "MESH data, last updated [date]"

## Color Coding
- Score ≥ 7: green (`#22c55e`)
- Score 5–6.9: yellow (`#eab308`)
- Score < 5: red (`#ef4444`)

## API Endpoint
`GET /hotels/{hotel_id}/eco-score` → returns full EcoScoreResponse with sub-scores
